HEADWORD: Proverbialist
<hw>Pro*ver"bi*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who makes much use of
proverbs in speech or writing; one who composes, collects, or studies
proverbs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proverbialize</ent>⟦br⟧
